==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pasty
<hw>Pas"ty</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Pasties</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OF. <ets>past⟦eacute⟧</ets>, F.
<ets>p⟦acir⟧t⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Paste</er>, and cf.
<er>Patty</er>.]</ety> <def>A pie consisting usually of meat wholly
surrounded with a crust made of a sheet of paste, and often baked
without a dish; a meat pie.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧If ye pinch me like a
<xex>pasty</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Apple
<xex>pasties</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Dickens.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A large <qex>pasty</qex> baked in a pewter platter.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pat</ent>⟦br⟧
